news.title: China establishes mortgage rate adjustment mechanism for some home buyers
news.para: For cities where the selling prices of new homes fall month-on-month and year-on-year for three consecutive months, the floor on mortgage rates can be lowered or abolished for first-time home buyers in phases, according to a statement by the People's Bank of China (PBOC).

news.title: Real estate broker Compass to cut more jobs to deal with housing downturn
news.para: Home sellers looking for buyers gave concessions in nearly 42% of home sales in the fourth quarter - the highest share in any three-month period, real estate broker Redfin said, citing its records in a report on Thursday.

news.title: CBRE defers 'around half' of Q3 UK property fund withdrawals
news.para: CBRE said in October it was deferring redemption requests made in the second quarter from the 1.7 billion pound ($2.02 billion) fund.
